OL,3,CWhat is the noble false widow and are
OL,4,Cspider bites on the rise in England?
OL,6,FFirst reported in southern England in
OL,7,F1879, the species originates from
OL,8,FMadeira and the Canary Islands.
OL,10,FAccording to the Natural History
OL,11,FMuseum, there are six species of
OL,12,Fspider in the UK, which are commonly
OL,13,Freferred to as false widow spiders:
OL,15,FThe Natural History Museum says noble
OL,16,Ffalse widow spiders have a body length
OL,17,Fof between seven and 14 millimetres,
OL,18,Fwith females typically larger than
OL,19,Fmales.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
