PN,30312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776103865
OL,3,CWhat is the noble false widow and are
OL,4,Cspider bites on the rise in England?
OL,6,F"No antivenom exists for this species,
OL,7,Fprincipally because its bite has not
OL,8,Fbeen shown to cause near-fatal or
OL,9,Ffatal outcomes," the charity added.
OL,11,FIf you're bitten, the venom in the
OL,12,Fbite can cause pain and itching, and
OL,13,Fthere may be localised swelling and
OL,14,Fminor symptoms such as short-term
OL,15,Fnausea and headaches, and tenderness
OL,16,Fat the bite site.
OL,18,FWhat to do if you get bitten?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776103865
OL,3,CWhat is the noble false widow and are
OL,4,Cspider bites on the rise in England?
OL,6,FBuglife, alongside Public Health
OL,7,FEngland and the British Arachnological
OL,8,FSociety, says that if you are bitten,
OL,9,Fthe bite should be cleaned with soap
OL,10,Fand water.
OL,12,FOral painkillers and ice packs can
OL,13,Fhelp to manage pain or discomfort from
OL,14,Fthe bite.
OL,16,FYou should get medical attention if
OL,17,Fyou notice severe swelling, feel
OL,18,Ffaint, feverish, or generally
OL,19,F"unwell", or if you experience
OL,20,Fcramping, sweating, or symptoms of an
OL,21,Fallergic reaction.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
